# Node Graph Viz (PyQt5)

Interactive 16-step sequencer visualization with a node-ladder waveform view.

- Left: vertical 16-step bar (one track/node)
- Right: waveform ladder (one lane per node; currently 1 lane)
- Load a local sample and toggle steps; a moving playhead indicates the current step

References: [miniaudio manual](https://miniaud.io/docs/manual/index.html), [node graph example](https://miniaud.io/docs/examples/node_graph.html)

## Requirements
- Python 3.9+
- `uv` package manager

## Quick start (uv)
```bash
# Install uv if not installed
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh

cd /Users/romansmirnov/projects/fortuned/tools/node_graph_viz
uv venv
. .venv/bin/activate
uv pip install -e .

# Run
uv run node-graph-viz
# or
uv run python -m node_graph_viz
```

## Notes
- Audio playback is optional and disabled by default. This tool focuses on visualization and step sequencing.
- If you want to experiment with audio later, install `miniaudio` and connect the `SequencerEngine` audio hooks.
